# Multimodal E-Commerce Intelligence Platform  
### Product Classification and Customer Sentiment Analysis

##  Project Overview

This project presents a **multimodal data analytics pipeline** designed for e-commerce intelligence using both **text and image data**. It focuses on three core tasks:

- Customer sentiment analysis from product reviews  
- Topic modeling and text understanding from multiple corpora  
- Image classification using CIFAR-10 dataset  

The system integrates classical Machine Learning, Deep Learning, and NLP techniques to extract insights from heterogeneous data sources.


##  Objectives

- Build a complete end-to-end data analytics pipeline
- Compare multiple NLP preprocessing and feature extraction techniques
- Evaluate sentiment analysis models on imbalanced datasets
- Perform topic modeling across heterogeneous text corpora
- Apply named entity recognition for structured text understanding
- Implement image classification using both classical and deep learning methods
- Compare HOG + PCA vs CNN-based image recognition



##  Datasets Used

- **20 Newsgroups Dataset** → Text classification and topic modeling  
- **Customer Reviews Dataset (CSV)** → Sentiment analysis  
- **Wikipedia Corpus** → Topic modeling (BERTopic)  
- **CIFAR-10 Dataset** → Image classification  



##  Methodology

### 1. Data Preprocessing
- Tokenization
- Stopword removal
- Stemming & Lemmatization
- Text normalization
- Image normalization (pixel scaling)

### 2. Feature Engineering
- Bag of Words (BoW)
- TF-IDF
- Word2Vec embeddings
- GloVe embeddings
- HOG features for images

### 3. Machine Learning Models
- Logistic Regression
- Linear SVC
- Random Forest

### 4. Deep Learning Models
- BiLSTM for sentiment analysis
- Custom CNN for CIFAR-10 classification

### 5. Topic Modeling
- Latent Dirichlet Allocation (LDA)
- Non-negative Matrix Factorization (NMF)
- BERTopic (Transformer-based)

### 6. Named Entity Recognition
- spaCy pre-trained NLP pipeline



##  Key Findings

- Lemmatization outperformed stemming in preserving semantic meaning  
- TF-IDF improved classification performance over raw BoW  
- Word2Vec and GloVe captured semantic relationships effectively  
- Severe class imbalance strongly impacted sentiment models  
- Accuracy alone is misleading for imbalanced datasets  
- CNN significantly outperformed HOG + PCA for image classification  
- BERTopic produced the most coherent topics among all models  



